  "power": {
    "description": "A Pokémon's Power comes from the combination of three things: species (base frame), IV (growth), and Quality (rarity).",
    "power_formula": "Power = (HP + Atk + Def + SpAtk + SpDef + Spd) × Quality",
    "stat_formula": "stat = round( (base + 2×growth) × level/100 × Quality^exp )",
    "notes": [
      "Quality appears twice (inside each stat and again in Power) — that's why it weighs so much.",
      "The IV enters only as 2×growth added to the species base, which dominates the stat.",
      "Between two Pokémon of the same species: if Quality differs significantly, higher Quality almost always wins even with lower IV. If Quality is similar, compare IVs.",
      "You can't find the strongest by multiplying tier × IV — that math is NOT how the game works."
    ]
  },
